\subsection{Robustness of the Zero-Shot Foundation}
Counter to prevailing literature, the Source Model exhibited remarkable cross-ethnic resilience, achieving an AUROC of 0.852. Crucially, the Oracle model---provided with full access to target-domain labels and hardware characteristics---performed at 0.892 AUROC. We attribute this to DINOv3's high-capacity extraction of structural features (optic disc/cup morphology) rather than relying on brittle color/lighting textures that CNNs typically overfit to.

